--- !u!114 &1247280683
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1247280681}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 1e70e461d96c70e419d8acefdd7c3edc, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::SlideUIController
  slideController: {fileID: 745187817}
  pageTextUI: {fileID: 2104998988}
  commonImageRect: {fileID: 2104998987}
  defaultAnchoredPosition: {x: 0, y: 0}
  defaultAnchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
  defaultAnchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
  defaultPivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
  pageUIData:
  - pageText: You have been provided with a sample of solid ammonium chloride. Let's
      study the change in its physical state upon heating.
    width: 753
    height: 150
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 0
  - pageText: Tap to select the required pieces of apparatus and materials.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: To begin the experiment, drag the watch glass containing the ammonium
      chloride salt towards the china dish and pour it in.
    width: 753
    height: 150
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 0
  - pageText: Now, drag the tripod stand to place it over the burner.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: Drag the wire gauze and place it on the tripod stand.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: Drag the china dish containing the given ammonium chloride and place
      it on the wire gauze.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: Drag the funnel towards the china dish to cover it.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: Drag the cotton plug towards the inverted funnel to insert it into
      its stem.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: 
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: Tap on the burner to start heating.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: 
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: 
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: The vapour pressure is used to measure the tendency of any substance
      to change into its gaseous state. It should be noted that a substance with
      a high vapour pressure at a particular temperature is often volatile, and it
      can easily sublime. Due to its high vapour pressure, a volatile solid has a
      greater tendency to vapourise, and hence, the liquid state of the sublimable
      solid is practically non- existent.
    width: 753
    height: 350
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 0
  - pageText: 
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: Now, let us observe how sublimation occurs at a molecular level.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: When we heat a sublimable solid, its particles gain sufficient kinetic
      energy and change into the gaseous state. This increases the vapour pressure
      over the solid surface. If a solid has sufficient vapour pressure at a given
      temperature, it can directly sublime into the air.
    width: 753
    height: 270
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 0
  - pageText: Drag the inverted funnel and keep it in the highlighted area.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: The vapours of ammonium chloride have been deposited on the inner wall
      of the funnel. This appears as solidified white ammonium chloride crystals.
    width: 753
    height: 150
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 0
  - pageText: 
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: Spatula to scrape and collect the crystals of ammonium chloride.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: 
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: Click on the dropdowns and select the correct answer.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
  - pageText: You have been provided with a sample of solid ammonium chloride. Let's
      study the change in its physical state upon heating.
    width: 753
    height: 137
    anchoredPosition: {x: 118, y: -35}
    anchorMin: {x: 0, y: 1}
    anchorMax: {x: 0, y: 1}
    pivot: {x: 0, y: 1}
    preserveAspect: 1
